    "created_at": "2017-04-14T00:22:43Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-04-14T00:23:07Z",
    "body": "@tejohnso WebViews are used to host remote content in their own renderer process.  This effectively creates a nested WebContents inside your top level BrowserWindow for every webview you have.  WebView's give access to webcontents API's, preload scripts and a whole load of other stuff that you shouldn' have access to if `nodeIntegration` is not enabled.\r\n\r\nThe trick here is that `nodeIntegration` **inside** the WebView is disabled, this means that you can have your browserwindow with nodeIntegration hosting remote content in a safe way.  This fulfills both the quoted pieces of documentation.\r\n\r\n1. The WebView which is hosting the remote content will have `nodeIntegration` disabled\r\n2. The renderer hosting the WebView will have `nodeIntegration` enabled"
  },
