    "updated_at": "2017-04-14T13:13:39Z",
    "body": "@MarshallOfSound I think I understand the situation.  Since the subordinate has privilege X, the superordinate must clearly indicate and expose its privilege X so as not to mask the existence of that privilege in the subordinate.\r\n\r\nHowever, I think the row I would expect is `\"Disabled | No | Yes | No\"`.  In fact, I think that's the **only** row I would expect.  A more flexible option would be to prevent nodeIntegration in a WebView whose parent does not also have nodeIntegration.  In the current state, we're prevented from the most restrictive option of ensuring nodeIntegration is disabled in the parent BrowserWindow as well as the child WebView."
  },
