    "updated_at": "2017-04-14T17:04:12Z",
    "body": "I think you got it backwards again.  `nodeIntegration: true` doesn't prevent it, it is an explicit way of allowing it.  `nodeIntegration: false` explicitly prevents the current renderer creating a webview and therefore prevents it from accessing node APIs through the webview APIs.\r\n\r\nI can only explain this so many times, I'd what I'm saying doesn't make sense for some reason I'd suggest asking on slack and seeing if someone else can explain it to you.\r\n\r\nThe easiest thing to say here.  Having a webview gives a renderer access to node APIs through a preload script on that webview.  If an existing renderer has node disabled giving it access to a webview allows it to bypass the disabling of node.  This is neither safe nor secure, hence only renderers with node enabled can use webviews"
  },
